FBIS4-48292 "drafr095_c_94015" FBIS-AFR-94-095 Daily Report 18 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Britain To Double Country's Aid to 500 Million Rands Britain To Double Country's Aid to 500 Million Rands MB1705062194 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 2000 GMT 16 may 94 MB1705062194 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network Afrikaans BFN [Text] Britain is to double its financial aid to South Africa to 500 million rands in the next three years. British Ambassador to South Africa Sir Anthony Reeve announced this in Durban and added that his government is eager to promote trade with South Africa. Sir Anthony said it is imperative that South Africa should not snub its traditional markets while it is exploring new markets in the Middle East.
